## Behavioral Risk Analysis

### Over-Utilization Desperation Risk

```sql
SELECT
    CASE
        WHEN revol_util >= 75.00
             AND inq_last_6mths >= 3
        THEN '1. Desperate: Maxed Cards + Credit Hunting'

        WHEN revol_util >= 75.00
             AND inq_last_6mths < 3
        THEN '2. High Utilization Only'

        WHEN revol_util < 50.00
             AND inq_last_6mths = 0
        THEN '3. Stable: Low Card Usage & No Inquiries'

        ELSE '4. Moderate Baseline Group'
    END AS consumer_behavior_profile,

    COUNT(*) AS total_borrowers,
    SUM(not_fully_paid) AS total_defaults,

    ROUND(
        AVG(not_fully_paid) * 100,
        2
    ) AS default_rate_percentage

FROM loan_portfolio

GROUP BY consumer_behavior_profile
ORDER BY consumer_behavior_profile;
```

